  "articleSummary": "In \"Into the Breach,\" the author argues that modern supply chain attacks exploit developers' laptops as \"credential warehouses,\" where a single bad click can exfiltrate browser cookies, SSH keys, cloud CLI configs, and AI tool context—making local security as critical as production. The tone is analytical and urgent, rejecting \"be careful\" as ineffective and framing humans as \"traffic,\" not boundaries. Key technical recommendations include enforcing Dev Containers by default to isolate project work and deploying canary tokens as digital tripwires for early detection. The intended audience is developers and security-conscious teams seeking high-leverage, practical defenses against credential theft and prompt injection.",
